decision_conditions:
The cell blocks and link corridor hereby permitted shall be removed and the land re-instated to its former condition as parking spaces on or before the date 18 months from the date of this permission.

Reason:  The buildings are not considered to be suitable as permanent structures in this location within the setting of a listed building, and so that their effect can be reviewed and to comply with Policies E3 and BD1 of this Council's Borough Wide Primary Policies Development Plan Document.
description: Temporary pre-fabricated single storey cells with associated secure link corridor to a door opening in the south wall of the prisoner van dock.
